	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg – A 47-year-old Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) officer is in a critical condition at Milpark Hospital after he was shot in the head by hijackers in the early hours of Tuesday morning in Booysens. JMPD spokesperson Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said the officer intervened after a minibus was hijacked at around 04:45 near Pat Mbatha Busway and Old True Road Booysens. Also read: 2 JMPD officers killed after drunk driver crashes into roadblock Minnaar said the officer was alone at the time. "The suspects shot at the officer about five times and one bullet hit the side of his head," Minnaar said. No arrests have been made.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  